<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - FRONT COVER, VIBRATION DAMPER, and GEROTOR OIL PUMP - Installation
        - Front Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26505.4.5" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Front Oil Seal and Wear Sleeve</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>A wear sleeve is not installed during engine production. The wear sleeve is required for rebuild
                    and is supplied with the front oil seal, as a service part only.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650531" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd07/D0747A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Liquid gasket application</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a 360&#176; bead of Loctite&#174; Hydraulic Sealant on the leading edge of the
                crankshaft before wear sleeve installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650532" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd06/D0647A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front oil seal and wear sleeve</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wear sleeve</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front oil seal</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Front Oil Seal/Wear Sleeve Installer</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use the Front Oil Seal/Wear Sleeve Installer , to drive oil seal and wear sleeve assembly
                into the oil pump cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
